.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/017-two-lane-opus-deep-review/review/deltas/iter-9.jsonl:2:{"type":"finding","id":"correctness-9-1","severity":"P1","dimension":"correctness","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs","line":153,"title":"Wired Lane B loop scores fixtures' own reference content against their own criteria; no model is invoked, dispatch-model.cjs is dead in the wired path, aggregate score is model-independent constant","evidence":"loop-host.planInvocation(model-benchmark) returns ONLY [materialize, run-benchmark] (loop-host.cjs:153-159). materialize writes each fixture's own content/markdown to {id}.md (materialize.cjs:36-58,91). run-benchmark scores that same {id}.md against the same fixture's requiredHeadings/requiredPatterns (run-benchmark.cjs:434-437). auto YAML phase_loop runs only loop-host (auto.yaml:147); no step writes model output into benchmark-outputs/{id}.md. Live: materialize+run-benchmark on default profile => aggregateScore 100, benchmark-pass, all rows 100. 5dim+llm reads the materialized reference file as outputText (run-benchmark.cjs:274), grading the reference, not a model candidate. dispatch-model.cjs is referenced in docs/README + loop-host RESOLVE set but never spawned by any plan/YAML step.","fix":"Insert a per-fixture dispatch step (call dispatch-model.cjs, overwrite {id}.md with model stdout) BEFORE run-benchmark scores it; OR if Lane B is intentionally fixture-self-validation, rewrite role/purpose/docs and remove the 'benchmark a model' framing + dispatch-model references; OR gate the loop so it does not emit a model verdict it never measured.","confidence":0.88,"iter":9}
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/017-two-lane-opus-deep-review/review/deltas/iter-9.jsonl:3:{"type":"finding","id":"correctness-9-2","severity":"P2","dimension":"correctness","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs","line":48,"title":"loop-host lists dispatch-model.cjs in LANE_MODEL_BENCHMARK resolve set but planInvocation never plans it, so its resolveScriptPath branch is unreachable","evidence":"LANE_MODEL_BENCHMARK = Set(['run-benchmark.cjs','dispatch-model.cjs']) (loop-host.cjs:48-51) and resolveScriptPath maps dispatch-model.cjs to ../model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs (79-81), but planInvocation only ever returns materialize + run-benchmark (130-159). No plan step names dispatch-model.cjs; the lane entry and resolver branch are unreachable from loop-host. This is the structural footprint of correctness-9-1.","fix":"Either wire the dispatch step (see correctness-9-1) or drop the unused dispatch-model.cjs entry from LANE_MODEL_BENCHMARK to remove the misleading 'it is wired' signal.","confidence":0.9,"iter":9}
