.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/017-two-lane-opus-deep-review/review/deltas/iter-1.jsonl:1:{"type":"finding","iter":1,"id":"correctness-1-1","severity":"P1","dimension":"correctness","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs","line":91,"title":"Fixture-id path traversal: 015 F-P1-9 guard only hardened run-benchmark.cjs, not the materializer that writes fixture outputs first","evidence":"materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs:91 does fs.writeFileSync(path.join(outputsDir, `${fixture.id}.md`), ...) with no sanitization. loop-host.cjs:155-158 runs the materializer BEFORE run-benchmark.cjs, and the auto YAML step_run_benchmark mirrors this. Empirically: a fixture with id=\"../escaped\" caused the materializer to write escaped.md OUTSIDE outputsDir (into its parent) and exit 0. The 015 regression test run-benchmark-hardening.vitest.ts:67-79 only calls runBenchmark without the materializer, so its `evil.md not created` assertion does not cover the real first-writer path; grep confirms zero materializer-traversal test coverage.","fix":"Port assertSafeFixtureId / SAFE_FIXTURE_ID from run-benchmark.cjs into materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs and call it before path.join(outputsDir, `${fixture.id}.md`) at line 91 (and ideally share one helper). Add a materializer hostile-id regression test.","confidence":"high","claim":"The 014 F-P1-9 fixture-id traversal class is only partially remediated: the guard exists in run-benchmark.cjs but not in the materializer, which is the first and actual writer of fixture output files in the model-benchmark plan.","evidenceRefs":[".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs:91",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs:155",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs:128",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/tests/run-benchmark-hardening.vitest.ts:67"],"counterevidenceSought":"Checked whether run-benchmark.cjs guard runs before any materializer write (it does not — separate process, runs second); checked for any sanitization or mkdir-guard inside the materializer (none); checked tests for materializer hostile-id coverage (none); ran empirical repro confirming the parent-dir escape write.","alternativeExplanation":"Could be argued benign because benchmark profiles are trusted-author content, so a hostile fixture id requires a malicious/compromised profile author. Rejected as a downgrade-to-P2 because the project itself treats the analogous criteria-exec surface (F-P1-3) as a real latent surface worth gating, and the 015 packet explicitly claimed to fix this exact traversal class — leaving the first writer unguarded is an incomplete remediation, not a non-issue.","finalSeverity":"P1","downgradeTrigger":"Downgrade to P2 if a documented invariant guarantees fixture ids are schema-validated against SAFE_FIXTURE_ID upstream (e.g. at profile load / fixture authoring) before materialization, OR if the materializer is provably never run on untrusted fixtures in any shipped path."}
