.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/017-two-lane-opus-deep-review/review/deltas/iter-2.jsonl:2:{"type":"finding","iter":2,"id":"security-2-1","severity":"P1","dimension":"security","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/bundle-gate.cjs","line":153,"title":"DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0 hardening gate does not cover bundle-gate.cjs; fixture acceptance.command still shell-executes via the D2 smoke-run path","evidence":"The 015 F-P1-3 criteria-exec gate was added ONLY in score-model-variant.cjs::scoreAcceptanceDeterministic (score-model-variant.cjs:107-113, skips execSync(a.command) for type=deterministic when DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0). But on the same 5dim pass, score() also spawns runDetCheck(bundle-gate, ...) (score-model-variant.cjs:209) and the virtual fixture carries acceptance: criteria.acceptance verbatim (lines 196,205). bundle-gate.cjs::scoreLayer3 (lines 128-157) selects acceptance with type smoke-run OR (deterministic AND command) and runs execSync(acceptance.command, {cwd: cwdAbs, timeout: 30000}) with NO check of DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC (the env var string is absent from bundle-gate.cjs entirely). SKILL.md:279 documents the flag as refusing criteria-driven shell execution in the 5-dim scorer; bundle-gate IS a 5-dim det-check (D2, weight 0.30, the hard gate), so the documented guarantee is false. The F-P1-3 test remediation.vitest.ts:119-131 only feeds type=deterministic acceptance through scoreAcceptanceDeterministic and never exercises bundle-gate Layer-3, so the gap is untested. Shipped default.json fixtures carry no command (dormant), but the surface goes live the moment any profile/fixture defines a smoke-run or deterministic+command acceptance under --scorer 5dim.","fix":"Route bundle-gate Layer-3 through the same env gate: either (a) bundle-gate.cjs::scoreLayer3 early-returns a skipped layer when process.env.DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC===0, or (b) score-model-variant.cjs strips acceptance[].command (and skips the bundle-gate smoke-run) before writing the virtual fixture when the flag is set. Add a type=smoke-run regression to remediation.vitest.ts asserting no execution under the flag.","confidence":"high","claim":"The 015 F-P1-3 criteria-exec hardening control is incomplete: it gates one of two shell-exec paths in the 5-dim scorer (scoreAcceptanceDeterministic) but not the second (bundle-gate Layer-3 smoke-run), so a hardened deployment that sets DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0 still executes fixture-supplied commands, contradicting SKILL.md:279.","evidenceRefs":[".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/bundle-gate.cjs:128",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/deterministic/bundle-gate.cjs:153",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs:107",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs:209",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:279",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/tests/remediation.vitest.ts:119"],"counterevidenceSought":"Grepped bundle-gate.cjs for DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC (absent); confirmed score-model-variant.cjs unconditionally calls runDetCheck(bundle-gate) regardless of the flag; confirmed the virtual fixture passes acceptance through unmodified; read remediation.vitest.ts F-P1-3 block and confirmed it only tests the scoreAcceptanceDeterministic path, never bundle-gate; checked shipped default.json fixtures and confirmed no command field (so dormant by default, not an open shipped exploit).","alternativeExplanation":"Could be argued benign because benchmark profiles are trusted-author content and the shipped fixtures define no command, so no exploit ships today. Rejected as a downgrade-to-P2: the project itself treats the analogous scoreAcceptanceDeterministic surface as a real latent P1 worth a gate, and the value of that gate is undermined if a parallel exec path ignores it. A documented security control that fails to cover its advertised scope is a real defect at the same severity as the surface it claims to protect.","finalSeverity":"P1","downgradeTrigger":"Downgrade to P2 if a documented invariant guarantees acceptance commands are schema-stripped/validated before reaching any det-check when DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0, OR if bundle-gate Layer-3 is provably unreachable on every shipped 5dim path."}
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/017-two-lane-opus-deep-review/review/all-findings.jsonl:1:{"type":"finding","iter":1,"id":"correctness-1-1","severity":"P1","dimension":"correctness","file":".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs","line":91,"title":"Fixture-id path traversal: 015 F-P1-9 guard only hardened run-benchmark.cjs, not the materializer that writes fixture outputs first","evidence":"materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs:91 does fs.writeFileSync(path.join(outputsDir, `${fixture.id}.md`), ...) with no sanitization. loop-host.cjs:155-158 runs the materializer BEFORE run-benchmark.cjs, and the auto YAML step_run_benchmark mirrors this. Empirically: a fixture with id=\"../escaped\" caused the materializer to write escaped.md OUTSIDE outputsDir (into its parent) and exit 0. The 015 regression test run-benchmark-hardening.vitest.ts:67-79 only calls runBenchmark without the materializer, so its `evil.md not created` assertion does not cover the real first-writer path; grep confirms zero materializer-traversal test coverage.","fix":"Port assertSafeFixtureId / SAFE_FIXTURE_ID from run-benchmark.cjs into materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs and call it before path.join(outputsDir, `${fixture.id}.md`) at line 91 (and ideally share one helper). Add a materializer hostile-id regression test.","confidence":"high","claim":"The 014 F-P1-9 fixture-id traversal class is only partially remediated: the guard exists in run-benchmark.cjs but not in the materializer, which is the first and actual writer of fixture output files in the model-benchmark plan.","evidenceRefs":[".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs:91",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs:155",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs:128",".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/tests/run-benchmark-hardening.vitest.ts:67"],"counterevidenceSought":"Checked whether run-benchmark.cjs guard runs before any materializer write (it does not — separate process, runs second); checked for any sanitization or mkdir-guard inside the materializer (none); checked tests for materializer hostile-id coverage (none); ran empirical repro confirming the parent-dir escape write.","alternativeExplanation":"Could be argued benign because benchmark profiles are trusted-author content, so a hostile fixture id requires a malicious/compromised profile author. Rejected as a downgrade-to-P2 because the project itself treats the analogous criteria-exec surface (F-P1-3) as a real latent surface worth gating, and the 015 packet explicitly claimed to fix this exact traversal class — leaving the first writer unguarded is an incomplete remediation, not a non-issue.","finalSeverity":"P1","downgradeTrigger":"Downgrade to P2 if a documented invariant guarantees fixture ids are schema-validated against SAFE_FIXTURE_ID upstream (e.g. at profile load / fixture authoring) before materialization, OR if the materializer is provably never run on untrusted fixtures in any shipped path."}
