 blends semantic search with graph-aware project context |\\n8: | 🔍 **Code Index + Graph** | Callers, imports, impact paths, and concept-based code discovery |\\n9: | 🤖 **11 Specialized Agents** | Focused roles for implementation, review, research, docs, git, and more |\\n10: | 🎯 **21 On-Demand Skills** | Skill Advisor routing for the right workflow at the right time |\\n11: \\n12: **Reasons to try it**\\n13: \\n14: [![GitHub Stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/MichelKerkmeester/opencode--spec-kit-skilled-agent-orchestration?style=for-the-badge&logo=github&color=fce566&labelColor=222222)](https://github.com/MichelKerkmeester/opencode--spec-kit-skilled-agent-orchestration/stargazers)\\n15: [![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/MichelKerkmeester/opencode--spec-kit-skilled-agent-orchestration?style=for-the-badge&color=7bd88f&labelColor=222222)](LICENSE)\\n16: [![Latest Release](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/MichelKerkmeester/opencode--spec-kit-skilled-agent-orchestration?style=for-the-badge&color=5ad4e6&labelColor=222222)](https://github.com/MichelKerkmeester/opencode--spec-kit-skilled-agent-orchestration/releases)\\n17: \\n18: - Works with **Opencode**, **Codex**, ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1779357340785,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_01_WiQjkMWCZ98WzrU9X2yg4460\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/AGENTS.md\",\"limit\":200},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/AGENTS.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AI Assistant Framework (Universal Template)\\n2: \\n3: > **Universal behavior framework** defining guardrails, standards, and decision protocols.\\n4: \\n5: ---\\n6: \\n7: ### Multi-Repository Architecture\\n8: \\n9: **Universal Framework:** Code work behavior is handled automatically by the `sk-code` skill, which routes between code surfaces detected at dispatch time. The active set of detection markers and per-surface patterns lives inside `sk-code` — see `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md` §2 Smart Routing for the current detection list and `references/<surface>/` for per-surface conventions.\\n10: \\n11: **How It Works:** `sk-code` detects the active code surface from CWD/target paths and library markers, loads patterns from `.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/<surface>/`, and selects surface-appropriate verification (see Quick Reference). Surfaces it does not recognize trigger a disambiguation question rather than guessing.\\n12: \\n13: **The Iron Law:** NO completion claims without running stack-appropriate verification.\\n14: \\n15: ---\\n16: \\n17: ## 1. 🚨 CRITICAL RULES\\n18: \\n19: ### Safety Constraints\\n20: \\n21: **HARD BLOCKERS (The \\\"Four Laws\\\" of Agent Safety):**\\n22: 1. **READ FIRST:** Never edit a file without reading it first. Understand context before modifying.\\n23: 2. **SCOPE LOCK:** Only modify files explicitly in scope. **NO** \\\"cleaning up\\\" or \\\"improving\\\" adjacent code. Scope in `spec.md` is FROZEN.\\n24: 3. **VERIFY:** Syntax checks and tests **MUST** pass before claiming completion. **NO** blind commits.\\n25: 4. **H... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1779357342570,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_02_JaAdhtOfrBDhHNW6gyiF6430\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/README.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/README.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: \\\"Skills Library\\\"\\n3: description: \\\"Canonical index of all skills in .opencode/skills/ with routing guidance, structure reference, and skill creation workflow.\\\"\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"skills library\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"available skills\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"skill overview\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"what skills exist\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"skill routing\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"skill advisor\\\"\\n11:   - \\\"available scripts\\\"\\n12:   - \\\"skill catalog\\\"\\n13:   - \\\"which skill should I use\\\"\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Skills Library\\n17: \\n18: > The complete inventory of on-demand AI capabilities available in this framework.\\n19: \\n20: Across this skill tree, `/speckit:resume` is the canonical recovery surface for Spec Kit packet work. Continuity still rebuilds from `handover.md`, then `_memory.continuity`, then the remaining spec docs, while generated memory artifacts remain supporting only.\\n21: \\n22: ---\\n23: \\n24: <!-- ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\\n25: ## TABLE OF CONTENTS\\n26: \\n27: - [1. OVERVIEW](#1--overview)\\n28: - [2. QUICK START](#2--quick-start)\\n29: - [3. FEATURES](#3--features)\\n30: - [4. STRUCTURE](#4--structure)\\n31: - [5. CONFIGURATION](#5--configuration)\\n32: - [6. USAGE EXAMPLES](#6--usage-examples)\\n33: - [7. TROUBLESHOOTING](#7--troubleshooting)\\n34: - [8. FAQ](#8--faq)\\n35: - [9. RELATED DOCUMENTS](#9--related-documents)\\n36: \\n37: <!-- /ANCHOR:table-of-contents -->\\n38: \\n39: ---\\n40: \\n41: <!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\\n42: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n43: \\n44: `.opencode/skills/` holds 19 skill folders. Skills are not passive references. E... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n6: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1779357344340,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_03_boiRtqfjyYTqdS75TRlg5782\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/README.txt\"},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/README.txt<