n10: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1779357350182,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e49f67922001JQnKMIE3Nz7W6H\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"97308bf776d6ff0932c9c32d468d6f901714a29a\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e49f617de001EtOvg1TF408p5D\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":41074,\"input\":38649,\"output\":407,\"reasoning\":98,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":1920}},\"cost\":0.06928506}}\n11: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1779357351636,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e49f67ed2001uRXmOA1Itqrtwx\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e49f67a080019jHrkfQuvpyOaA\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"snapshot\":\"40104904ec98389061e15222477793f672eee9b6\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n12: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1779357361542,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_00_0FkzANCkQt2GukKqzbDb0747\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/AGENTS.md\",\"offset\":201},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/AGENTS.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n201: - **Options:** A) Existing | B) New | C) Update related | D) Skip | E) Phase folder (e.g., `specs/NNN-name/001-phase/`)\\n202: - **Router commands:** For router-style commands such as `/doctor`, evaluate Gate 3 per selected route. The route manifest/table must expose each target's location and mutation class (`read-only`, `add-only`, `mutates`) before asking or acting.\\n203: - **Ask first, then act.** No Read/Edit/Write/Bash (except Gate Actions) before answer. The answer applies for the ENTIRE session — re-ask ONLY when user says \\\"new task\\\" / \\\"different feature\\\" / names a different spec folder, or asks you to re-ask.\\n204: \\n205: Router command manifests must make the mutation boundary visible before execution:\\n206: - `read-only` routes may inspect and report without a spec-folder write path.\\n207: - `add-only` routes may create scoped logs, snapshots, or evidence after Gate 3 is satisfied.\\n208: - `mutates` routes require the same spec-folder discipline as any other file/database mutation.\\n209: \\n210: #### GATE 4: SKILL-OWNED WORKFLOW TIEBREAKERS\\n211: Trigger-phrase routing (\\\"deep-research\\\", \\\"deep-review\\\", \\\":auto\\\", \\\"iterations\\\", \\\"convergence\\\") and state-machine discipline (no manual `/tmp` state, no direct `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` Task dispatch, no skipping `deep-research-state.jsonl` / `deltas/` / `logs/`) are enforced by Gate 2 (Skill Advisor at ≥ 0.8) plus the `/deep:start-research-loop` and `/deep:start-review-loop` skill SKILL.md invariants. The two tiebreakers below are NOT covered there:\\n212: - **... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n13: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1779357363607,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1b609ea01ffeiHcdyR4tGQ6LMX\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_01_OYPKOn1Mr8ri08E3p9x10232\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/README.md\",\"offset\":729},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/README.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n729:                       ▼\\n730:            ┌──────────────────────┐\\n731:       5.   │  RENDER              │  Either a one-line hook brief\\n732:            │                      │  or a JSON recommendation list\\n733:            └──────────┬───────────┘\\n734:                       ▼\\n735:                 RESULT:\\n736:            advisor_recommend -> list of skill recommendations\\n737:            hook adapter -> \\\"Advisor: live, use ...\\\"\\n738:            shim fallback -> legacy JSON\\n739: ```\\n740: \\n741: &nbsp;