     4	allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task
     5	---
     6	
     7	> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL — READ FIRST**
     8	>
     9	> This command runs a structured workflow. Do NOT dispatch agents from this document.
    10	>
    11	> **YOUR FIRST ACTION:**
    12	> 1. Run Phase 0: @general agent self-verification (below)
    13	> 2. Run Setup Phase: consolidated prompt to gather inputs
    14	> 3. Determine execution mode from user input (`:auto` or `:confirm`)
    15	> 4. Load matching YAML workflow and execute
    16	>
    17	> This command is **general-agent based** — orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill invocation.
    18	
    19	---
    20	
    21	# 🚨 PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION
    22	
    23	**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**
    24	
    25	```
    26	EXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):
    27	
    28	SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?
    29	│
    30	├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:
    31	│   ├─ You can orchestrate deep-agent-improvement invocation
    32	│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution
    33	│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic
    34	│
    35	├─ IF YES (all indicators present):
    36	│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to Setup Phase
    37	│
    38	└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:
    39	    │
    40	    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED
    41	    │
    42	    ├─ DISPLAY to user:
    43	    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    44	    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │
    45	    │   │                                                            │
    46	    │   │ This command orchestrates deep-agent-improvement skill     │
    47	    │   │ invocation and runs general-agent based.                   │
    48	    │   │                                                            │
    49	    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │
    50	    │   │   /deep:start-agent-improvement-loop [arguments]           │
    51	    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
    52	    │
    53	    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR="General agent required"
    54	```
    55	
    56	**Phase Output:**
    57	- `general_agent_verified = ________________`
    58	
    59	---
    60	
    61	# 🔒 UNIFIED SETUP PHASE
    62	
    63	**FIRST MESSAGE PROTOCOL**: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt MUST be your FIRST response. No implementation or file-modifying tool calls before asking. Lightweight read-only discovery to suggest a spec folder or load prior context is allowed, then ask ALL questions immediately and wait.
    64	
    65	For `:auto`, do not emit the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup with the three-tier branch below, then load the auto YAML only after all required values are bound.
    66	
    67	### `:auto` Setup Resolution
    68	
    69	Setup contract: see `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md`.
    70	
    71	Under `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` (from the `:auto` suffix), follow the three-tier flow:
    72	
    73	1. **Tier 1 — Resolve confidently** (contract §1): parse `$ARGUMENTS` flags + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` block (§2) + the Default Resolution Table below (§3). When every required field is resolved, persist to `{spec_folder}/improvement/agent-improvement-config.json` (shape: `targetPath`, `targetProfile`, `specFolder`, `executionMode: "auto"`, `scoringMode`, `maxIterations`, `agentName`), bind runtime YAML placeholders, set `STATUS: PASSED`, load `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_auto.yaml`. End §0.
    74	
    75	2. **Tier 2 — Targeted ask** (contract §1): when 1-2 required fields are genuinely ambiguous AND no default exists, emit ONE narrow question per ambiguous field. Command-specific Tier-2-eligible fields (per the Default Resolution Table below): `spec_folder`. **Ordering rule**: none needed; `target_path` absence is missing input, not ambiguity, and goes to Tier 3.
    76	
    77	3. **Tier 3 — Fail fast** (contract §4): emit the named-missing-inputs error format with `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop:auto` as the command name. Exit non-zero. Do not load YAML.
    78	
    79	`:confirm` path stays unchanged — see the consolidated setup prompt section below.
    80	
    81	### PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS Schema (for `:auto` non-interactive dispatch)
    82	
    83	The dispatched prompt body may contain one structured marker block. Parse it before applying defaults. Grammar: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2.
    84	
    85	```yaml
    86	PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:
    87	  lane: agent-improvement  # optional; one of: agent-improvement | model-benchmark; defaults to agent-improvement when an agent path is present
    88	  target_path: .opencode/agents/debug.md  # required path matching .opencode/agents/*.md
    89	  target_profile: dynamic  # optional; one of: handover | context-prime | dynamic; derived from target_path when omitted
    90	  spec_folder: specs/041/008  # required spec folder path or explicit runtime folder
    91	  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS  # from :auto suffix
    92	  scoring_mode: dynamic  # dynamic is the current supported scoring mode
    93	  max_iterations: 5  # positive integer
    94	```
    95	
    96	Rules: see `auto_mode_contract.md` §2 (unspecified fields fall back to default; marker fields take precedence over $ARGUMENTS flags; unknown fields warn; malformed lines parse-error).
    97	
    98	### Default Resolution Table
    99	
   100	| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |
   101	|-------|----------|--------------|---------|------------------|
   102	| `lane` | Y | explicit flag `--lane` or marker `lane` resolved FIRST (an explicit `--lane=model-benchmark` that conflicts with a supplied agent path fails fast or asks one disambiguation, never silently picks Lane A). Then agent-path presence -> `agent-improvement`. Then benchmark-profile or `--profile` arg -> `model-benchmark` | `agent-improvement` when an agent path is present and no explicit lane | N |
   103	| `target_path` | Y | `$ARGUMENTS` agent path, or marker `target_path` | none | N |
   104	| `target_profile` | Y | marker `target_profile`, or auto-detect from `target_path` (`handover` -> `handover`, `context-prime` -> `context-prime`, otherwise `dynamic`) | inferred from `target_path` | N |
   105	| `spec_folder` | Y | flag `--spec-folder`, marker `spec_folder`, or requires-ask | none | Y |
   106	| `execution_mode` | Y | attached suffix `:auto` or marker `execution_mode` | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | N |
   107	| `scoring_mode` | Y | marker `scoring_mode`, Q3 equivalent, or default | `dynamic` | N |
   108	| `max_iterations` | Y | flag `--iterations`, marker `max_iterations`, or default | `5` | N |
   109	
   110	**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**
   111	
   112	**🚨 SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT - ONE USER INTERACTION**
   113	
   114	This workflow uses a SINGLE consolidated prompt to gather ALL required inputs in ONE user interaction.
   115	
   116	**Round-trip optimization:** This workflow requires only 1 user interaction for setup.
   117	
   118	```
   119	EXECUTE THIS SINGLE CONSOLIDATED PROMPT:
   120	
   121	1. CHECK for mode suffix in $ARGUMENTS or command invocation:
   122	   ├─ ":auto" suffix detected → execution_mode = "AUTONOMOUS" (pre-set, omit Q2)
   123	   ├─ ":confirm" suffix detected → execution_mode = "INTERACTIVE" (pre-set, omit Q2)
   124	   └─ No suffix → execution_mode = "ASK" (include Q2 in prompt)
   125	
   126	1B. RESOLVE lane BEFORE the agent-path check (additive; default is Lane A).
   127	   Evaluate EXPLICIT lane signals (--lane flag or marker lane) FIRST, before any
   128	   agent-path inference, so an explicit lane is never shadowed (F-P1-8):
   129	   ├─ IF explicit --lane=model-benchmark OR marker lane=model-benchmark
   130	   │     ├─ AND an agent path (.opencode/agents/*.md) is ALSO present → CONFLICT:
   131	   │     │     do NOT silently pick a lane. Fail fast with a one-line conflict error,
   132	   │     │     or ask ONE disambiguation question ("Explicit --lane=model-benchmark
   133	   │     │     conflicts with the supplied agent path. Which lane?"). Resolve before proceeding.
   134	   │     └─ ELSE → lane = "model-benchmark" → AUTO-ROUTE (see Lane B routing below).
   135	   ├─ IF explicit --lane=agent-improvement OR marker lane=agent-improvement
   136	   │     → lane = "agent-improvement", omit Q(lane), proceed exactly as today (Lane A).
   137	   ├─ IF NO explicit lane AND $ARGUMENTS contains an agent path (.opencode/agents/*.md)
   138	   │     → lane = "agent-improvement" (CMD-1: agent path with no explicit lane still
   139	   │       auto-resolves to Lane A unchanged), omit Q(lane), proceed as today.
   140	   ├─ IF NO explicit lane AND a --profile arg / benchmark-profile is present (no agent path)
   141	   │     → lane = "model-benchmark" → AUTO-ROUTE (see Lane B routing below).
   142	   └─ IF neither lane signal nor an agent path present AND interactive (no :auto)
   143	         → include Q(lane) as the FIRST question in the consolidated prompt and resolve it before Q0.
   144	
   145	   Lane B routing: AUTO-ROUTE to the dedicated model-benchmark workflow:
   146	   load .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_{auto,confirm}.yaml
   147	   (see /deep:start-model-benchmark-loop). Subsequent questions become the Lane B set
   148	   (profile, outputs/spec_folder, exec, scoring_method, grader, executor+model).
   149	   DO NOT ask Q0/Q1/Q3 (the agent-improvement questions).
   150	
   151	2. CHECK if $ARGUMENTS contains an agent path (Lane A only; skipped when lane=model-benchmark):
   152	   ├─ IF present (.opencode/agents/*.md) → target_path = detected value, omit Q0
   153	   └─ IF missing → include Q0 in prompt
   154	
   155	3. CHECK for --spec-folder flag:
   156	   ├─ IF present → spec_folder = value, omit Q1
   157	   └─ IF missing → include Q1 in prompt
   158	
   159	4. CHECK for --iterations flag:
   160	   ├─ IF present → max_iterations = value
   161	   └─ IF missing → max_iterations = 5 (default)
   162	
   163	5. List available agents for Q0:
   164	   $ ls .opencode/agents/*.md
   165	
   166	6. List recent spec folders for Q1:
   167	   $ ls -d specs/*/ 2>/dev/null | tail -10
   168	
   169	7. ASK user with SINGLE consolidated prompt (include only applicable questions):
   170	
   171	   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
