     1	AGENTS DIRECTORY
     2	================
     3	
     4	This directory contains agent definitions for the OpenCode runtime.
     5	Each .md file defines one live agent surface with frontmatter (tools, permissions, model)
     6	and behavioral instructions.
     7	
     8	Sibling runtimes: .claude/agents/ (.md), .gemini/agents/ (.md), .codex/agents/ (.toml)
     9	Inventory rule: if an agent file is not present in this directory, it is not a live runtime surface here.
    10	
    11	Agents:
    12	  code          — Application-code implementation (write-capable LEAF; sk-code stack delegation)
    13	  create    — /create:* documentation executor (write-capable LEAF; sk-doc templates; caller-restricted)
    14	  context       — Retrieval-first codebase exploration
    15	  debug         — Fresh-perspective debugging
    16	  deep-research — Autonomous research iterations
    17	  deep-review   — Autonomous code review iterations
    18	  deep-agent-improvement — Evaluator-first bounded agent improvement
    19	  prompt-improver — Prompt engineering
    20	  orchestrate   — Multi-agent coordination
    21	  review        — Code review (read-only)
    22	  ai-council   — Multi-strategy planning

