     3	description: Sentinel for small-model optimization patterns covering SWE-1.6 + DeepSeek-v4-pro + Kimi-k2.6 + Qwen3.6 + GLM-5.1 + MiniMax-2.7 across cli-devin and cli-opencode (DeepSeek API + opencode-go + MiniMax.io direct API providers) dispatch paths. Routing anchor only; real patterns live in cli-devin/references/ and cli-opencode/references/.
     4	allowed-tools: []
     5	version: 0.1.0
     6	---
     7	
     8	<!-- Keywords: small-model, swe-1.6, deepseek-v4, kimi-k2.6, qwen3.6, glm-5.1, minimax-2.7, minimax-api, haiku, gemini-flash, opencode-go, deepseek-api, context-budget, output-verification, model-profiles, structured-permissions, quota-fallback -->
     9	
    10	# Small-Model Optimization Sentinel
    11	
    12	A discovery anchor that surfaces alongside `cli-devin` or `cli-opencode` whenever a small-model task is dispatched, then points operators at the executor-owned patterns.
    13	
    14	---
    15	
    16	## 1. WHEN TO USE
    17	
    18	### Activation Triggers
    19	
    20	**Use when**:
    21	- Dispatching to SWE-1.6 (Cognition free tier) via `cli-devin`
    22	- Dispatching to DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.6, or GLM-5.1 (Cognition Pro plan) via `cli-devin`
    23	- Dispatching to DeepSeek-v4-pro directly via `cli-opencode` + DeepSeek API provider (`DEEPSEEK_API_KEY`, `--pure` required)
    24	- Dispatching to DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.6, Qwen3.6, or GLM-5.1 via `cli-opencode` + opencode-go provider (workspace credit pool)
    25	- Dispatching to MiniMax-2.7 via `cli-opencode` + MiniMax.io direct API provider (`MINIMAX_API_KEY`, `--model minimax/MiniMax-M2.7`, separate `minimax-api` quota pool)
    26	- Optional future targets: Claude Haiku (Anthropic separate quota), Gemini Flash (Google separate quota)
    27	- Asking "where is the small-model X pattern?" — context budget, output verification, model profiles, structured permissions, quota fallback
    28	
    29	**Keyword Triggers**:
    30	- `small model`, `small-model dispatch`
    31	- Model names: `swe-1.6`, `kimi-k2.6`, `deepseek-v4`, `qwen3.6`, `glm-5.1`, `minimax-2.7`, `haiku`, `gemini flash`
    32	- Provider names: `opencode-go`, `deepseek-api`, `minimax` / `minimax-api`, `cognition pro`, `cognition free`
    33	- Pattern names: `context budget`, `output verification`, `model profile`, `structured permissions`, `quota fallback`, `tool scoring`
    34	
    35	### Use Cases
    36	
    37	#### Routing Anchor
    38	
    39	Surface as a co-recommendation when `cli-devin` or `cli-opencode` is already the primary skill. The advisor reaches this skill through `enhances` edges from both CLI skills, providing one obvious entry point regardless of which executor is in use.
    40	
    41	#### Pattern Discovery
    42	
    43	Operators read `references/pattern-index.md` to find the canonical location of each small-model pattern. The index lists ownership (which CLI skill owns the pattern) and shipping status per phase.
    44	
    45	### When NOT to Use
    46	
    47	**Do not use for**:
    48	- Frontier-model dispatch (Opus, Sonnet, gpt-5.5) — those are out of scope for the 114 arc
    49	- Bulk copying of pattern bodies into other skills — the patterns are runtime-specific to their executor
    50	- Adding new runtime logic — this sentinel is documentation routing only
    51	
    52	---
    53	
    54	## 2. SMART ROUTING
    55	
    56	### Primary Detection Signal
    57	
    58	Discovery happens through skill-advisor `enhances` edges + trigger phrases, not a dedicated detection script.
    59	
    60	```text
    61	Operator prompt mentions small-model name or pattern
    62	    |
    63	    +-- Advisor matches trigger phrases (lexical lane)
    64	    +-- cli-devin or cli-opencode already high-confidence
    65	    +-- enhances edge pulls sk-prompt-small-model into top-3
    66	```
    67	
    68	### Phase Detection
    69	
    70	```text
    71	TASK CONTEXT
    72	    |
    73	    +- STEP 0: Identify whether a small-model executor is involved
    74	    +- STEP 1: Surface sk-prompt-small-model alongside the executor skill
    75	    +- Phase 1: Read references/pattern-index.md
    76	    +- Phase 2: Navigate to the executor-owned pattern file
    77	    +- Phase 3: Apply the pattern from its canonical location
    78	```
    79	
    80	### Resource Domains
    81	
    82	```text
    83	references/
    84	    pattern-index.md      # The only reference; lists owners + ship status
    85	```
    86	
    87	This skill intentionally has no `assets/` and no `scripts/`. The patterns themselves live in:
    88	
    89	- `.opencode/skills/cli-devin/references/` and `assets/`
    90	- `.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/` and `assets/`
    91	- `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/assets/` (model-profiles registry)
    92	- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/` (runtime helpers)
    93	
    94	### Resource Loading Levels
    95	
    96	| Level       | When to Load             | Resources                     |
    97	| ----------- | ------------------------ | ----------------------------- |
    98	| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation   | `references/pattern-index.md` |
    99	| CONDITIONAL | Operator names a pattern | Follow link from index to executor-owned file |
   100	| ON_DEMAND   | Adopting Haiku/Flash     | Update the index + executor metadata (see README) |
   101	
   102	### Smart Router Pseudocode
   103	
   104	The sentinel has no runtime routing of its own. Routing is performed by the skill-advisor through `graph-metadata.json` edges:
   105	
   106	```python
   107	# Conceptual — the actual scorer lives in system-skill-advisor
   108	def surface_sk_prompt_small_model(prompt, advisor):
   109	    if matches_trigger(prompt, SMALL_MODEL_TRIGGERS):
   110	        # Lexical lane match
   111	        return ("sk-prompt-small-model", advisor.lexical_score(prompt))
   112	    if "cli-devin" in advisor.top_k(prompt, k=3) or "cli-opencode" in advisor.top_k(prompt, k=3):
   113	        # Graph_causal lane via enhances edge (weight 0.5)
   114	        return ("sk-prompt-small-model", 0.5 * advisor.enhances_weight)
   115	    return None
   116	```
   117	
   118	Operators do not invoke a router from inside this skill. They follow `references/pattern-index.md` to the executor-owned file.
   119	
   120	---

