+5. Treat `@deep-agent-improvement` as the main unresolved naming decision. If the proposal-only mutator remains agent-only, keeping the agent command name may be semantically defensible; if the agent name becomes `@deep-improvement`, runtime mirrors and stress-test playbooks need a coordinated update. Record this in Phase 002 `decision-record.md` before edits. [SOURCE: .opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md:24] [SOURCE: .opencode/agents/deep-agent-improvement.md:26] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/002-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md:48]
+
+# Open Questions
+
+1. Should the proposal-only mutator be renamed from `@deep-agent-improvement` to `@deep-improvement`, or should only the parent skill rename while the agent keeps its precise Lane A role?
+
+2. Should advisor expose `deep-agent-improvement` as a deprecated alias indefinitely, or only through a transitional compatibility window?
+
+3. Should Phase 002 update `feature_catalog` and `manual_testing_playbook` only for rename correctness, leaving the two-lane to three-lane rewrite to Phase 004, or should it add minimal Lane C placeholders to avoid another doc churn pass?
+
+4. Should generated/archive metadata under old spec packets be left untouched with a grep allowlist, or should `descriptions.json` receive normalized keywords for current search while preserving historical descriptions?
